{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"CreativeWork","name":"Using API Platform with Docker","text":"\u003ch1\u003eUsing API Platform with Docker\u003c/h1\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eProjects using API Platform can be run through \u003ca href=\"https://www.docker.com/\"\u003eDocker\u003c/a\u003e and\n\u003ca href=\"https://docs.docker.com/compose/\"\u003eDocker compose\u003c/a\u003e. Run \u003ccode\u003edocker-compose up -d\u003c/code\u003e,\nyour project will be accessible at \u003ca href=\"http://127.0.0.1\"\u003ehttp://127.0.0.1\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou can customize Docker configuration by creating your own \u003ccode\u003edocker-compose.yml\u003c/code\u003e\nfile. For example, if you want Nginx to run on port 8888:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-yaml\"\u003eweb:\n    image: vincentchalamon/docker-symfony\n    ports:\n        - 8888:80\n    volumes:\n        - .:/var/www\n    tty: true\n\ndb:\n    image: mysql\n    command: mysqld --port 3386\n    net: \u0026#34;host\u0026#34;\n    environment:\n        MYSQL_DATABASE: api\n        MYSQL_USER: root\n        MYSQL_ALLOW_EMPTY_PASSWORD: yes\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n","author":[{"@type":"Person","Name":"Kévin Dunglas","email":"dunglas@gmail.com"},{"@type":"Person","Name":"Kévin Dunglas","email":"dunglas@gmail.com"},{"@type":"Person","Name":"Stepan Anchugov","email":"kixxx1@gmail.com"}],"dateCreated":"2015-09-04T13:21:53+02:00","dateModified":"2015-09-22T13:36:13+05:00"}